The paper deals with the problem of establishing dense correspondences within a set of related shapes, which is a common problem in computer graphics and computer vision. The proposed method involves optimization and statistical shape modeling, which are techniques commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with mesh processing and generative modeling, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.GR (Computer Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves learning algorithms and optimization techniques, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
